  "body": "I was doing some experiments with visibility specifiers and noticed that constructor functions can be defined as `internal`. This causes the contract to be marked as abstract, but child contracts can call the super constructor without problems.\r\n\r\nAre there any real world use cases of this? Is it something we would like to support?",
